summary of key insights from this session data analytics is not just about building dashboard in minutes or hour it is a minor part of data analyst work it is not that easy for freshers or anyone to get a da job as it is glorified on the internet as of aug there is a huge competition and limited roles a fresher should do something outstanding to get recruiters attention like having a solid project portfolio online credibility on linkedin cold emailing messaging on linkedin to get recommendations etc do not buy any paid course directly if you have no idea about this field spend days on solid research learn from free resources first to understand if you like this role do more research about market condition most importantly do not blindly believe anyone on the internet do your own research offline networking can be a game changer for both freshers people with career break and experienced people from wanting to transition career check for the offline events near your place and join them job guarantee pay after placement get lpa all these are scams running in the market if you do not pay time extra for research you will loose both your money and time domain knowledge is key freshers can domain knowledge by starting with business kpis understanding the business process behind the apps use checking customer stories on microsoft following case studies solving unguided projects check codebasics resume project challenges this wont completely replace the need for practical experience but it will be better than having no experience people with career gap or transitioning career should try to combine their past domain experience with their tool skills to make a strong resume and apply for roles particular to that domain for example a person with sales experience in telecom domain should have projects particular to that domainfunction to show relevant experience and also maintain the salary range there are more insights in this video watch it fully if you are interested

overview of generative ai evolution from statistical ml to deep learning with neural networks transformers have led to a variety of powerful ai models buddy is a stochastic parrot with mimicking ability and statisticsbased predictions understand vector database and semantic search word to numeric representation using word embeddings retrieval augmented generation rag allows finetuning or building ai models on specific data sets using gpt for querying data sources to work with gen ai you need models cloud services and frameworks llm based application using openai api creating separate keys for different projects and managing them securely using llm to generate creative restaurant names based on cuisine preferences implementing simple sequential chain concept in gen ai course using sequential chains to get both restaurant name and menu items in gen ai course setting up streamlit for application development using response data to display restaurant name and menu items in ui practice coding while watching the video gen ai has a reasoning component for answering questions beyond its knowledge using gen ai to retrieve information about elon musks age in initializing environment variables and using ai tools in an agent using conversation chain to optimize cost and memory optimize openai token cost by limiting conversational buffer memory research analysts provide detailed stock research for companies like tata motors and reliance importance of building a specialized tool over using chat gpt using semantic search for finding relevant text chunks utilizing vector databases for faster search and retrieval installing and loading lang chain library in jupyter notebook providing explanation about the moviescsv file contents text splitting and merging for efficient processing using lang chain provides a simple api for text splitting text splitting process using separators and size constraints gen ai course explains recursive text splitter and merging for chunk optimization demonstration of using libraries to convert text into vectors using meditation and yoga to improve mental health with vector representation gen ai performs semantic search to provide results based on context not just keywords retrieval qa with sources chain creating open api embeddings for document retrieval using a vector database and creating a retrieval chain for text analysis assembling the final project with prebuilt individual pieces loading environment variables and creating basic ui in gen ai module saving data in memory and displaying progress setting up vector database and creating retrieval qa chain in python automated news research tool for equity analysts utilizing vector databases for storing embeddings in large projects utilizing google palm and sql database chain in lang chain framework introduction to vector database and google palm for ai applications explaining the tshirt records and database setup setting up a sql database object with uri understanding the importance of correct database mapping for accurate results learning to run and manage queries in db chain summing of stock quantities for white color tshirts storing data into arrays and using hugging face embedding for generating embeddings vector store converts input questions into embeddings for similarity matching import sql prompt template to generate queries enhanced querying functionality with additional parameters creating a streamlit ui with few lines of code creating a main function in python and running sql queries in a database chain using streamlet to ask and answer questions efficiently

i saw that some people in the comments are having an issue with typeerror cannot pickle threadrlock object i was also getting the same error and after doing some research i came up with this get around let me know if this solution helps you as well this is dhavals code to store the results of the vector index storing results of the vector index filepath vectorindexpkl with openfilepath wb as f pickledumpvectorindexopenai f here is my modification storing results of the vector index filepath vectorindexpkl with openfilepath wb as f pickledumpvectorindexopenaiserializetobytes f this is dhavals code to read the results of the vector index from the pickle file opening the file if ospathexistsfilepath with openfilepath rb as f vectorindex pickleloadf here is my modification opening the file if ospathexistsfilepath with openfilepath rb as f uploadedpickle pickleloadf vectorindex vectorindexopenaideserializefrombytesserializeduploadedpickle embeddingsembeddings im assuming the reason for this error is that in later versions of langchain the embedding result of vectorindexopenai is being stored as an object in order to write it as a pickle file it first needs to be serialized into bytes vice versa when the pickle file is being read it needs to be deserialized let me know if this solution helps you as well

heres a general overview of how ai systems like llms work data collection ai systems are trained on vast amounts of data for language models this often includes text from books articles websites and other sources the quality and diversity of the training data greatly influence the models performance preprocessing text data goes through preprocessing steps such as tokenization where the text is divided into smaller units tokens these tokens could be words subwords or even characters depending on the model model architecture llms are built on transformer architectures transformers use selfattention mechanisms that allow the model to weigh the significance of different words in a sentence concerning each other capturing longrange dependencies in the data layers of transformers process the input data allowing the model to learn complex patterns in the text training during training the model is fed input data and learns to predict the next word or token in a sequence this is done iteratively adjusting the models internal parameters weights through backpropagation and optimization algorithms to minimize prediction errors inference after training the model can generate text based on the patterns it learned during the training process users input a prompt and the model generates a response based on its understanding of the language from the training data postprocessing generated text might go through postprocessing steps to improve readability or ensure that it fits a specific format deployment trained models can be deployed in various applications such as chatbots language translation services content generation and more deployment involves integrating the model into software applications allowing users to interact with it hope this comment is helpful and give users to more insight do let us know
